<main>
  <div id="intro" class="container">
    <p>
      Have you always wanted to learn Korean so that you could visit Korea, understand what they're saying in K-pop songs, or watch Korean dramas without subtitles?
    </p>
    <p>
      Well, you're going to need to learn the Korean alphabet first. You can try this 
      <a href="<%= asset_path('alphabet.jpg')%>" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">comic</a> 
      or some 
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=learn+korean+alphabet" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">YouTube videos</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you're like me and already know the alphabet, then you can use this site to improve your vocabulary and memorize common phrases.
    </p>
    <p>
      Scroll down, choose a deck of flashcards, and get learning!
    </p>
  </div>

  <div id="categories" class="container-fluid">
    <h1>Decks</h1>
    <% @alldecks.each do |deck| %>
        <%= link_to deck.name, deck, :class => "item" %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</main>